Including Plots

Plots : Understanding the distribution of different variables : 1. Cylinders - 2. Engines 2. Transmission 3. Manufactures 4. Carlines 5. DriveSystems

  1. Most cars have 4,6,8 cylinders , highest being 4 cylinder cars.
  2. Majoirty of cars Engine displacement ranging from 2 to 3.5
  3. Semi automatic cars are highest followed by automatic and manual
  4. GM is the leading manufacturer of cars driven followed by BMW and Toyota
  5. 2 wheel drive and All wheel drive are higher than 4 wheel drive cars
  6. Types of cars - midsize cars are highest in numbere followeed buy compact and sub compact.

Understanding the impact of different variables on fuel usage : - lower the cylinders, the better is the fuel consumption. - CVT cars have better fuel consumption (mpg) , better than manual - Mazda gives highest mpg, Honda and Subaru have next better mpg.. The average mpg for Volkswagon, BMW and Toyota are same but Toyota does have better max mpg. - Order of better mpg, from highest to lowest - Small station wagons, compact cars, small suvs, mini cars, suvs and trucks. - 2 wheel front drive cars have better mpg than other drive systems.

Impact of mpg on GHG rating : - Higher fuel economy is associated with better GHG emissions.
